
MesoScan - Mesolens Laser Scanning Microscope Application
---------------------------------------------------------

The Embarcadero Delphi XE Integrated Development Environment is required to build this package.

This package also requires the shared set components (SESComponentsXE) used by the Strathclyde Electrophysiology software to be installed first. If it is not already installed on the Delphi toolbar, install it by ...

1) Extract the components from the johndempster/SESComponents GitHub repository to the folder ....\Libraries\Documents\RadStudio\Projects\SESComponentsXE

2) Add the folder to the Delphi XE library path.

Select Delphi XE Tools/Options
Select the "Delphi Options: Library" panel
Click "..." at the right of Library Path, click the Add button and add "....\Libraries\Documents\RadStudio\Projects\SESComponentsXE" to the library 

3) Build and install the SESComponents package of components on the Delphi toolbar.

Select File/Open Project
Select Files of Type "*.dpk"
Select the "SESComponentsXE" Folder
Select "SESComponents.dpk"
Select Project/Build SESComponents
Select Components/Install Packages, click the ADD button and select the file ..\Libraries\Documents\RAD Studio\10.0\BPL\SESComponents.BBL

To open the Mesoscan project:

1) Extract the MesoCam project from the johndempster/MesoCamXE GitHub repository to the folder ..\Libraries\Documents\RAD Studio\MesoCamXE

2) To open the WinFluor project

Select File/Open Project
Select Files of Type "*.dpr"
Select the "MesoCam" Folder
Select "Mesoscan"
Click the Open button

